article.description: Hudson Price made all four of his 3-pointers and scored 23 points, Jon Davis added three 3s and 22 points, and Charlotte beat Elon 100-95 on Monday night.
article.headline: Charlotte scores 100-plus in consecutive games, beats Elon
article.linkText: Charlotte scores 100-plus in consecutive games, beats Elon
article.story: ELON, N.C. -- Hudson Price made all four of his 3-pointers and scored 23 points, Jon Davis added three 3s and 22 points, and Charlotte beat Elon 100-95 on Monday night. Charlotte (2-0) scored 101 points in its season-opening victory last Friday. Steven Santa Ana gave Elon its largest lead of the second half, 73-67, with 10:19 remaining, but Charlotte scored the next eight points to take a 75-73 lead. Elon never led again. Price hit a 3-pointer with 5:32 remaining for an eight-point lead and after Elon pulled to 91-89, Davis sank two free throws and Price made another 3-pointer with 39 seconds left for a 96-89 lead. Anthony Vanhook had 16 points and eight rebounds for Charlotte (2-0), while Braxton Ogbueze added 10 points. The 49ers hit 10 of 14 3-pointers. Santa Ana made five 3-pointers and scored a career-best 32 points for Elon (1-1), which was 9 of 26 from distance. Karolis Kundrotas added 16 points, and Brian Dawkins and Tyler Seibring had 10 points apiece.
